  "body": "### Description\n\nI just stumbled upon the fantastic Quarkus component test feature. It just has one flaw: While it's totally fine to set multiple config properties via `@TestConfigProperty` on the test class itself the same is not possible on test methods:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/assets/61313842/b2ba9b58-3cf6-4d16-9e36-5adc9ac2d8d9)\r\n\r\nUnfortunately I like to override multiple values in a specific test method. The current workaround is to create another test class with the config I need.\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nI'm not sure if setting `@Target({ TYPE, METHOD })` on `io.quarkus.test.component.TestConfigProperty.TestConfigProperties` is enough but I'm pretty sure that adding this feature cannot be hard.",
